task_description: Facing the building to your North-West (approx. 317°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roofline.
I can see the roofline, but now I need to see the base of the building to get a sense of the full height, so I will look down.

I have now viewed the top (pitch 30°) and the bottom (pitch -30°) of the building, and based on the visible floors, I estimate the ground floor is about 4 meters high and the five floors above are about 3 meters each, totaling approximately 19 meters.
